claim.claim-text:
A system for partitioning temperature controlled volumes, comprising:
a storage compartment having a plurality of storage positions at different heights, the temperature controlled compartment having an access side;
an insulating wall disposed along the access side, the insulating wall comprising a plurality of separable bricks slidably stacked within a plurality of vertical guides to define a plurality of columns, wherein each brick has a recess formed in its front face;
a tray shuttle compartment disposed along a side of the insulating wall opposite the storage compartment, the tray shuttle compartment enclosing a robotics mechanism for removing trays from and replacing trays into the plurality of storage positions, wherein the robotics mechanism has a lifting pin that aligns with and fits within the recess in a brick that is located nearest to a pre-determined storage position, lifts the brick and any bricks stacked on top of the brick to open a gap in the insulating wall, retrieves or replaces a tray from or into the rack by reaching through the gap, and lowers the lifted bricks to close the gap after the tray has been retrieved or replaced.

A method for accessing a sample storage tray in a rack in a storage compartment from a tray shuttle compartment, comprising:
stacking a plurality of bricks to a height sufficient to fully separate the storage compartment from the tray shuttle compartment, wherein each brick has a recess formed in a face exposed to the tray shuttle compartment;
aligning a lifting pin on a tray shuttle with the recess in one of the plurality of bricks that is located most closely to a tray of interest;
inserting the lifting pin into the recess and lifting the brick and any bricks stacked on the top of the one brick;
retrieving the tray of interest from the rack; and
returning the lifted bricks to the stack to re-enclose the storage volume.
